VI. A Description of the English Province of Carolana, by the Spaniards call'd Florida, and by the French La Louisiane. As also of the great and famous River Meschasebe, or Missisippi, the five vast Navigable Lakes of fresh Water, and the Parts adjacent. Together with an Account of the Commodities of the Growth and Production of the said Province. And a Preface containing some Considerations on the Consequences of the French making Settlements there. By
Daniel Coxe
, Esq;
